  "text": "Casual BP at rest was recorded in the upright seated position between 7 and 11 AM after an overnight fast in strict accordance with American Heart Association guidelines as described in detail previously by our laboratory [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Recordings were obtained in triplicate in three separate sessions at least one week apart in order to establish the stability of baseline levels; this was repeated at endintervention. The mean values from the three sessions were used to establish pre-and end-intervention levels. To avoid any possibility of investigator bias, recordings were obtained over the brachial artery with a semi-automated device (Dinamap XL, Critikon, Florida). Casual recordings of BP at rest also were obtained manually using auscultation over the brachial artery with a random zero sphygmomanometer",
